`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:'IIIT Bhagalpur attracts summer applicants because its labs blend core engineering with translational work tied to industry and national missions. This playbook focuses on how to win a seat in 2026: where to look, when to outreach, and how to avoid the common mistakes that sink otherwise strong profiles. Any date or stipend notes marked as "Expected / Indicative" mirror recent cycles and help you move early; update your plan when official circulars post.'}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"If you have limited time, prioritize three moves: (1) shortlist labs and write lab-specific pitches; (2) ship one fresh artifact or small reproduction per target lab; (3) prepare logistics (NOC, hostel plan, travel) so you can accept quickly. These three steps alone raise conversion dramatically versus generic CV blasts."}),`
